Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.print

Interface Printer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PrinterImpl
    public interface Printer
extends org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService

    The Printer service can be used to send resources to the client's printer queue.

    Please Note: Printing is an asynchronous operation. For this reason you need to attach a PrintListener to the Printer service to receive print results.

    Since:
    1.4
    No Implement:
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.

    • Method Detail

      • print

        void print​(java.lang.String url,
           java.lang.String jobName)

        Sends a print job to the client. The client will be instructed to print the resource defined in the url parameter.

        Parameters:
        url - the location of the resource to print. Must not be null or empty.
        jobName - the name of the printing job

      • addPrintListener

        void addPrintListener​(PrintListener listener)

        To get notified when about print results you can add a PrintListener. The listener will be called when the job succeeded, failed or was canceled.

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to add. Must not be null.

      • removePrintListener

        void removePrintListener​(PrintListener listener)

        Removes a PrintListener. The removed listener will no longer get print notifications.

        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to remove. Must not be null.
